Install audio multimodal runtime deps (librosa + backends) into the image.

Omni models whose perception path decodes audio need `librosa` at RUNTIME, e.g.
nvidia/Nemotron-3-Nano-Omni-30B-A3B-Reasoning-* — SGLang's model class
NemotronH_Nano_Omni_Reasoning_V3 (python/sglang/srt/models/nano_nemotron_vl.py,
get_audio_feature()) loads audio via librosa (Parakeet encoder front-end).
Upstream SGLang does NOT declare librosa as an install dependency, so an audio
request fails at runtime with ModuleNotFoundError while text + image/video work.
The model card's own SGLang note says "librosa must be installed first".

Mirrors the dockerfile-kernels-pin.patch mechanism: adds an `ARG AUDIO_DEPS`
plus a gated RUN step in the builder stage (BEFORE directory_split2.sh, so the
packages are carried into the runtime stage exactly like the kernels pin). The
install is a normal (with-deps) `uv pip install` so librosa pulls soundfile /
audioread / numba / llvmlite. Empty AUDIO_DEPS = no-op, so text/vision-only
images stay slim — only recipes that set AUDIO_DEPS get the audio stack.

Applied AFTER dockerfile-sm121.patch and dockerfile-kernels-pin.patch (it
anchors on the kernels-pin block), same as the other dgxarley Dockerfile
patches. The recipe drives it via the AUDIO_DEPS variable (see
sglang-0.5.13-sm121.recipe). Remove if/when upstream SGLang adds librosa to the
multimodal extras and the build installs that extra.

Apply to: container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly in the local clone of
scitrera/cuda-containers.

--- a/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
+++ b/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
@@ -256,6 +256,19 @@
         uv pip install --force-reinstall --no-deps kernels==${KERNELS_VERSION}; \
     fi

+# dgxarley: audio multimodal deps for omni models that decode audio at runtime
+# (e.g. nvidia/Nemotron-3-Nano-Omni-* — SGLang nano_nemotron_vl.py
+# get_audio_feature() -> librosa; upstream SGLang does NOT install it, so audio
+# input fails without this). Gated by the recipe's AUDIO_DEPS var; empty string
+# = no-op so text/vision-only images stay slim. Plain (with-deps) install so
+# librosa pulls soundfile/audioread/numba. See patches/dockerfile-audio-deps.patch.
+ARG AUDIO_DEPS=""
+RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
+    if [ -n "$AUDIO_DEPS" ]; then \
+        echo "=== Installing audio deps: ${AUDIO_DEPS} ==="; \
+        uv pip install ${AUDIO_DEPS}; \
+    fi
+
 # SM121 (DGX Spark GB10) shared memory fix for cutlass_moe_fp4.
 # Patches run_fp4_blockwise_scaled_group_mm_sm120() in the JIT-compiled
 # nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh to use KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecializedCooperative
